## âœ¨ Features

### Core Functionality
- âœ… **Task Management**
  - Add new tasks
  - Mark tasks as completed
  - Delete tasks
  - Filter tasks (All, Active, Completed)
  - Persistent storage using localStorage

- ğŸ‘¥ **User Directory**
  - Fetch users from JSONPlaceholder API
  - Search users by name or email
  - Pagination with 6 users per page
  - Loading and error states

- ğŸ¨ **Theme Switcher**
  - Light/Dark mode toggle
  - Persistent theme preference
  - Smooth theme transitions

### Technical Features
- **Component Architecture** - Reusable Button, Card, Navbar, and Footer components
- **State Management** - React hooks (useState, useEffect, useContext)
- **Custom Hooks** - useLocalStorage for data persistence
- **API Integration** - RESTful API calls with error handling
- **Responsive Design** - Mobile-first approach with Tailwind CSS
- **Modern UI/UX** - Smooth animations and hover effects

## ğŸ› ï¸ Technologies Used

- **React 18** - Frontend framework
- **Vite** - Build tool and development server
- **Tailwind CSS** - Utility-first CSS framework
- **Lucide React** - Modern icon library
- **JSONPlaceholder API** - Mock REST API for testing
- **localStorage** - Client-side data persistence

## ğŸ“‹ Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed:
- **Node.js** (v18.0.0 or higher)
- **npm** (v9.0.0 or higher) or **yarn** (v1.22.0 or higher)

Check your versions:
```bash
node --version
npm --version
```

## ğŸš€ Installation & Setup

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/react-task-manager.git
cd react-task-manager
```

### 2. Install Dependencies
```bash
npm install
# or
yarn install
```

### 3. Start Development Server
```bash
npm run dev
# or
yarn dev
```

The application will open at `http://localhost:5173`

### 4. Build for Production
```bash
npm run build
# or
yarn build
```

### 5. Preview Production Build
```bash
npm run preview
# or
yarn preview
```

